Inkex / Inkscape
----------------

  - querying inkscape for the bounding boxes of nested groups doesn't work
  - add a get_all_inkscape_bboxes method
  - guarantee that the external inkscape command is the same as the calling
    one? => inkscape could define an environment variable INKSCAPE_COMMAND
    when calling an extension
  - method for performing inkscape actions (--action) directly from inkex?


GENERAL
=======

  - automatic tests => look at the way official extensions are tested using
    pytest
  - add automatic testing using github actions

  - create French / English github releases using github actions

  - find a way to deal with existing / default values when changing
    configuration

  - abort extensions if they take too long???

  - translate to French

  - write documentation in .md files so that we can point to the git repo
    somewhere

  - evaluate different free online documentation hosting solutions (readthedoc
    and the like) and use github actions to deploy it

  - config options for OK / WARNING / ERROR colors

  - tagged element could receive a new description ("<desc>") for easy
    selection in inkscape (Ctrl-f)
      => it should be removed when cleaning artefacts
      => ideally, it should keep existing descriptions (prefix those messages
      with a special prefix???)
    => it's probably best to never modify existing objects

  - when several languages (menus) are installed, we could have an option
    "make this language the default" in expert -> config
    it would
      - copy menus-LANG to menus
      - rename <name>Dynalab - LANG</name> to <name>Dynalab</name>
      - remove the "make this language the default" entry


